CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 20, 1938, p.13, reads: "Elsie Brown in days of old sirens lured men's ships to the rocks, but here's a modern siren who could make 'em take to the ships. The lovely Miss Brown of South Hills is perched on the bow of the  Steamer St.  Paul during the Frogs boatride - Photo by Harris"Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, September 6, 1938, pg. 22, reads: "Rather easy to look at Miss Elsie Brown, member of Pittsburgh's Deb League, poses for a lens man on the Frog's annual boat ride."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Elsie Brown seated on bow of Steamer St. Paul during FROGS Club boat ride
